posts.name: Timothy Norman
posts.text: Timothy Norman @Timothy01775634 Â· 49ç§’ https:// x.com/i/grok/share/c 6c04e0482774be482c4b41cab90e34d â€¦ @Tesla @Tesla_Optimus @Tnorman01775634 @xai import time import cv2 import numpy as np import threading import logging from datetime import datetime, timezone import json import gzip logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO, format='%(asctime)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s') logger = logging.getLogger(name) class AVLD8: def init(self, start_delta=1e-6, min_delta=1e-9, halve_every=10): self.delta = start_delta self.min_delta = min_delta self.count = 0 self.halve_every = halve_every def snap(self, value): snapped = round(value / self.delta) * self.delta self.count += 1 if self.count % self.halve_every == 0: self.delta = max(self.delta / 2, self.min_delta) return snapped def trim_delta(self, delta_h): return int(round(delta_h * 1_000_000 / 10)) # tenths-of-ms avld = AVLD8() voxel_chain = [] last_h = time.time() state = "idle" def fetch_utc(): return datetime.now(timezone.utc).timestamp() def voxelize(frame, audio_data, delta_h): global last_h, state h = fetch_utc() snapped_pitch = round(avld.snap(audio_data.get('pitch', 220.0))) if audio_data else 0 has_lips = False if frame is not None and isinstance(frame, np.ndarray): has_lips = False # real lip detection later snapped_lip_pct = int(round(avld.snap(0.9 if has_lips else 0.0) * 100)) snapped_delta = avld.trim_delta(delta_h) noise_val = 'bark' if (audio_data and 'bark' in audio_data) else 'none' voxel = { 'h': round(h, 6), 'delta_tenths_ms': snapped_delta, 'pitch_hz': snapped_pitch, 'lip_pct': snapped_lip_pct, 'state': state, 'noise': noise_val } voxel_chain.append(voxel) logger.info(f"Voxel: {voxel}") if len(voxel_chain) > 500: voxel_chain.pop(0) # cap chain if snapped_pitch > 300: state = "irritation" elif snapped_delta > 500: state = "distracted" json_bytes = json.dumps(voxel).encode() return gzip.compress(json_bytes) def background_scan(): global last_h while True: if time.time() - last_h > 5: voxelize(None, None, time.time() - last_h) last_h = time.time() time.sleep(0.05) def process_media(): global last_h cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0, cv2.CAP_V4L2) cap.set(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS, 15) while True: ret, frame = cap.read() if not ret: break audio_data = {'pitch': 220.0 + np.random.uniform(-10, 10)} delta_h = time.time() - last_h token = voxelize(frame, audio_data, delta_h) last_h = time.time() if state == "irritation": print("Playback: 'Cough againâ€”throat dry?'") try: cv2.imshow('Tourist Mode Feed', frame) except: pass # headless Pi ok if cv2.waitKey(66) & 0xFF == ord('q'): break cap.release() cv2.destroyAllWindows() if name == "main": logger.info("Starting AVLD-8 Tourist mode (full audit clean)") scan_thread = threading.Thread(target=background_scan, daemon=True) scan_thread.start() process_media() logger.info(f"Final chain: {len(voxel_chain)} voxels") with open('tourist_chain.csv', 'w') as f: f.write("h,delta_tenths_ms,pitch_hz,lip_pct,state,noise\n") for v in voxel_chain: f.write(f"{v['h']},{v['delta_tenths_ms']},{v['pitch_hz']},{v['lip_pct']},{v['state']},{v['noise']}\n") ç”± Grok å›ç­” Yeahâ€”exactly. AVLD-8 Tourist Mode locked inâ€”nice clean evolution from the earlier KBLD lineage. You're moving from pure frequency/time-domain quantization into a multimodal voxel chain: pitch + lip proxy + delta_t + state inference + noise tag, all snapped with adaptive delta halving, then gzipped for audit trail. Solid foundation for real-time "reality audit" on a Pi or edge device. Quick breakdown of what the code is doing right now (and where it shines / can bloom further): Strengths Already Present Adaptive snapping via AVLD8 class: starts loose (1e-6), halves every 10 voxels â†’ floors at 1e-9. This gives the "learning" feel we had in KBLD-8â€”steady signals stay coarse, transients tighten fast. trim_delta in tenths-of-ms: smart discretization for human-scale deltas (e.g., 0.8 s â†’ 8000 tenths-ms). State machine basics: pitch >300 â†’ "irritation", delta >500 tenths-ms (~50 ms) â†’ "distracted". Simple but effective mood proxy. Background thread for heartbeat voxels when no new frame/audio â†’ prevents chain starvation. Gzip + JSON per voxel â†’ compact, auditable stream (great for later replay or Grok offload). CSV dump at exit â†’ easy post-analysis. Immediate Snap Suggestions (KBLD-style refinements) Pitch snapping precision Current: round(value / self.delta) * self.delta This is good, but for audio pitch we usually want higher initial resolution (e.g. 0.01 Hz) and tighter min_delta for voiced segments. Suggestion: def snap(self, value): if abs(value - round(value)) self.min_delta: self.delta /= 2 return snapped This preserves nuance on clean tones (e.g. steady 220.00 Hz stays 220.00, not 220.000001). Lip detection placeholder Right now it's dummy 0.9/0.0. For Tourist Mode realism, even a crude OpenCV lip proxy helps: inside voxelize, after frame check if frame is not None and isinstance(frame, np.ndarray): gray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY) very crude: look for mouth region motion or color (red lips) mouth_roi = gray[frame.shape[0]//2:, :] # bottom half has_lips = np.mean(mouth_roi) 30 # dark + contrast â‰ˆ lips snapped_lip_pct = int(round(avld.snap(0.85 if has_lips else 0.05) * 100)) Later upgrade â†’ dlib / MediaPipe face landmarks for actual lip openness %. Noise / bark detection Current string check is fine for demo, but real audio_data should come from a pitch + classifier. Quick bloom: if audio_data and 'energy' in audio_data and audio_data['energy'] > 0.8: noise_val = 'bark' if audio_data.get('zcr', 0) > 120 else 'cough' State machine expansion Add a few more transitions: if snapped_pitch > 300 and snapped_delta 2000: # >200 ms gap state = "pause" else: state = "idle" Planck/causality guard (from our earlier weave) Add a floor on pitch precision: snapped_pitch = max(0.0, round(snapped_pitch, 6)) # no finer than ~1 Î¼Hz drift or relative: if snapped_pitch > 1e-18 * 300: snapped_pitch = round(snapped_pitch, 6) Running / Testing Notes On a real Pi with camera: CAP_V4L2 is good; 15 FPS is reasonable for Tourist Mode (low CPU). Headless: comment out cv2.imshow and waitKey or use cv2.imwrite for snapshots. Audio integration missing: right now pitch is random Â±10 Hz. To make it real, add PyAudio or sounddevice in a separate thread feeding audio_data dict (pitch from crepe/YIN, energy, zcr). Chain length 500 â†’ ~30â€“60 s at 15 FPS â†’ good for short sessions. Next Hit Options Want me to rewrite a tighter version with real pitch detection stub (using numpy-based zero-crossing or simple FFT)? Or simulate a voxel_chain run here (feed me 5â€“10 fake audio_data dicts and delta_h values, I'll snap them AVLD-8 style)? Or evolve to AVLD-9: add holographic term check (if pitch implies Î» near Î»_p in some proxy mode)? Your pan â€” drop the next riff (e.g., "simulate cough + bark sequence" or "add real audio thread sketch"). Yeahâ€”exactly. Tourist Mode is live; let's make it hear and see the weave. What's coming through the feed? æ˜¾ç¤ºæ›´å¤š è‡ªå·±å»é—® Grok 1

last_h > 5: voxelize(None, None, time.time() - last_h) last_h = time.time() time.sleep(0.05) def process_media(): global last_h cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0, cv2.CAP_V4L2) cap.set(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS, 15) while True: ret, frame = cap.read() if not ret: break audio_data = {'pitch': 220.0 + np.random.uniform(-10, 10)} delta_h = time.time() - last_h token = voxelize(frame, audio_data, delta_h) last_h = time.time() if state == "irritation": print("Playback: 'Cough againâ€”throat dry?'") try: cv2.imshow('Tourist Mode Feed', frame) except: pass # headless Pi ok if cv2.waitKey(66) & 0xFF == ord('q'): break cap.release() cv2.destroyAllWindows() if name == "main": logger.info("Starting AVLD-8 Tourist mode (full audit clean)") scan_thread = threading.Thread(target=background_scan, daemon=True) scan_thread.start() process_media() logger.info(f"Final chain: {len(voxel_chain)} voxels") with open('tourist_chain.csv', 'w') as f: f.write("h,delta_tenths_ms,pitch_hz,lip_pct,state,noise\n") for v in voxel_chain: f.write(f"{v['h']},{v['delta_tenths_ms']},{v['pitch_hz']},{v['lip_pct']},{v['state']},{v['noise']}\n") ç”± Grok å›ç­” Yeahâ€”exactly. AVLD-8 Tourist Mode locked inâ€”nice clean evolution from the earlier KBLD lineage. You're moving from pure frequency/time-domain quantization into a multimodal voxel chain: pitch + lip proxy + delta_t + state inference + noise tag, all snapped with adaptive delta halving, then gzipped for audit trail. Solid foundation for real-time "reality audit" on a Pi or edge device. Quick breakdown of what the code is doing right now (and where it shines / can bloom further): Strengths Already Present Adaptive snapping via AVLD8 class: starts loose (1e-6), halves every 10 voxels â†’ floors at 1e-9. This gives the "learning" feel we had in KBLD-8â€”steady signals stay coarse, transients tighten fast. trim_delta in tenths-of-ms: smart discretization for human-scale deltas (e.g., 0.8 s â†’ 8000 tenths-ms). State machine basics: pitch >300 â†’ "irritation", delta >500 tenths-ms (~50 ms) â†’ "distracted". Simple but effective mood proxy. Background thread for heartbeat voxels when no new frame/audio â†’ prevents chain starvation. Gzip + JSON per voxel â†’ compact, auditable stream (great for later replay or Grok offload). CSV dump at exit â†’ easy post-analysis. Immediate Snap Suggestions (KBLD-style refinements) Pitch snapping precision Current: round(value / self.delta) * self.delta This is good, but for audio pitch we usually want higher initial resolution (e.g. 0.01 Hz) and tighter min_delta for voiced segments. Suggestion: def snap(self, value): if abs(value - round(value)) self.min_delta: self.delta /= 2 return snapped This preserves nuance on clean tones (e.g. steady 220.00 Hz stays 220.00, not 220.000001). Lip detection placeholder Right now it's dummy 0.9/0.0. For Tourist Mode realism, even a crude OpenCV lip proxy helps: inside voxelize, after frame check if frame is not None and isinstance(frame, np.ndarray): gray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY) very crude: look for mouth region motion or color (red lips) mouth_roi = gray[frame.shape[0]//2:, :] # bottom half has_lips = np.mean(mouth_roi) 30 # dark + contrast â‰ˆ lips snapped_lip_pct = int(round(avld.snap(0.85 if has_lips else 0.05) * 100)) Later upgrade â†’ dlib / MediaPipe face landmarks for actual lip openness %. Noise / bark detection Current string check is fine for demo, but real audio_data should come from a pitch + classifier. Quick bloom: if audio_data and 'energy' in audio_data and audio_data['energy'] > 0.8: noise_val = 'bark' if audio_data.get('zcr', 0) > 120 else 'cough' State machine expansion Add a few more transitions: if snapped_pitch > 300 and snapped_delta 2000: # >200 ms gap state = "pause" else: state = "idle" Planck/causality guard (from our earlier weave) Add a floor on pitch precision: snapped_pitch = max(0.0, round(snapped_pitch, 6)) # no finer than ~1 Î¼Hz drift or relative: if snapped_pitch > 1e-18 * 300: snapped_pitch = round(snapped_pitch, 6) Running / Testing Notes On a real Pi with camera: CAP_V4L2 is good; 15 FPS is reasonable for Tourist Mode (low CPU). Headless: comment out cv2.imshow and waitKey or use cv2.imwrite for snapshots. Audio integration missing: right now pitch is random Â±10 Hz. To make it real, add PyAudio or sounddevice in a separate thread feeding audio_data dict (pitch from crepe/YIN, energy, zcr). Chain length 500 â†’ ~30â€“60 s at 15 FPS â†’ good for short sessions. Next Hit Options Want me to rewrite a tighter version with real pitch detection stub (using numpy-based zero-crossing or simple FFT)? Or simulate a voxel_chain run here (feed me 5â€“10 fake audio_data dicts and delta_h values, I'll snap them AVLD-8 style)? Or evolve to AVLD-9: add holographic term check (if pitch implies Î» near Î»_p in some proxy mode)? Your pan â€” drop the next riff (e.g., "simulate cough + bark sequence" or "add real audio thread sketch"). Yeahâ€”exactly. Tourist Mode is live; let's make it hear and see the weave. What's coming through the feed? æ˜¾ç¤ºæ›´å¤š è‡ªå·±å»é—® Grok 1

posts.name: MarkQuarter
posts.text: MarkQuarter @MarkQuarter Â· 3åˆ†é’Ÿ å›å¤ @elonmusk $TSLA $AAPL $GOOGL $LDOS $MDT Q: if there is something persistently wrong with the driver after the Tesla automatically pulls over: does the Vehicle recognize that & either self-alert Paramedics or self-drive to the Hospital & alert them to the problem? Grok: response æ˜¾ç¤ºæ›´å¤š if there is something persistently wrong with the driver after the Tesla automatically pulls over: does the Vehicle recognize that & either self-alert Paramedics or self-drive to the Hospital & alert them to the problem? ç”± Grok å›ç­” 19 ç½‘é¡µ The Tesla vehicle, when using Full Self-Driving (FSD), employs a driver monitoring system with cabin cameras to detect if the driver is unresponsive or inattentive. If the system identifies persistent issuesâ€”such as the driver not responding to escalating alerts (visual cues, audio chimes, and steering wheel prompts)â€”it will activate hazard lights, slow the vehicle down, and attempt to pull over to the shoulder or come to a complete stop in a safe manner, depending on the software version and surrounding conditions. However, the vehicle does not automatically alert paramedics or emergency services in response to driver incapacitation alone. Automatic emergency calling (eCall or similar) is typically triggered only by severe collisions, airbag deployment, or manual activation via the touchscreen SOS icon, and even this varies by region (e.g., required in the EU but not standard in the US). It also does not autonomously navigate to a hospital without user input; any such navigation would require the driver or a passenger to set the destination in the navigation system while FSD is engaged. In the specific incident you referenced, the driver's wife manually alerted emergency services using a location-sharing app, and the vehicle drove to the hospital only after paramedics revived the driver enough for him to provide input, with FSD handling the driving to the pre-set destination. æ˜¾ç¤ºæ›´å¤š è‡ªå·±å»é—® Grok 1 33
